pr_body:
This PR solves issue #2 which adds a kill run button that will kill all jobs in the current run. It currently uses a mock API endpoint for success alert, needs to be connected to the teuthology-api

pr_title: src/routes: Update pydantic dict() to model_dump()
pr_body: `.dict()` method for converting a pydantic BaseModel to a dictionary is deprecated. This PR updates it to the new method, `.model_dump()`

This PR fixes #3 by adding appropriate function docstrings for every endpoint, and an example request body for pydantic schemas.

- [x] `/kill`
- [ ] `/suite`
- [ ] `/login`
- [ ] `/logout`

pr_title: pages/Job/index.jsx: Add sanity check for started time
pr_body: This PR solves #26 by adding a function to check whether a date is valid or not using `isValid` function of `date-fns` library. This function is further used in timeSince and returns N/A if the date is not valid.

pr_title: ./github/workflows/signed.yaml: Create CI for checking signed commits
pr_body: This PR fixes #6 using a bash script that checks for `Signed-off-by:` trailer in git commits. The script does not check the merge commits as they generally don't have the `Signed-off-by:` trailer.

pr_title: src/lib/paddles.ts: Add VITE_ prefix to env variables
pr_body: This PR fixes issue #34 by adding the `VITE_` prefix to `PADDLES_SERVER` variable.

In the release of `pydantic` version 2, the developers have created a separate library for settings and config class called `pydantic-settings`, more information can be found here: https://docs.pydantic.dev/latest/usage/pydantic_settings

This PR adds `pydantic-settings` as a dependency in requirements.txt and update from `pydantic` in `src/config.py`

pr_title: public/favicon.ico: Update favicon to pulpito icon
pr_body:
This PR solves issue #8 where the favicon was the same as the Ceph icon but is now replaced with the original Pulpito site logo.

![pulpito-white](https://github.com/ceph/pulpito-ng/assets/58616444/7daeb3b9-cbec-48b7-a9d4-461cbb2140b0)

pr_title: lib/utils.js: changed year format from yy to yyyy
pr_body: This PR is a fix for issue #9 where the date was initially in the format `yy-mm-dd hh:mm:ss` and the year was changed to `yyyy` format.
